From 1960 to 1980, the marriage rate increased in Minnesota from 6.9 to 9.2 per 1,000 population.
From 1980 to 2000, the marriage rate in Minnesota declined 26 percent from 9.2 per 1,000 to 6.8 per 1,000 population.
